Im building a new mage, she is already at lvl 28, but i just realized that mages dont get some a type of snare/root. Is this true or did i miss something?<br>
<br>
Is there items or quest items that we can buy or quest for to get snare/root? Any ideas would be of help.<br>
<br>
Thank you in Advance<br>
Kijira <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2399<br> <font color=#333333>(11/24/02 2:45:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7956.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Root/Snare</span><hr size=1> This topic comes up often.<br>
<br>
The only easy way for mages to get root is through <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Rocky the Big Ole Dirt Pile</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  One technique is to send in your earth pet, and pull him back after root sticks, only sending him back in to root.  This may be a good soloing technique for the planes.<br>
<br>
There are some items with 1-2 charges of root or snare.  Check the equipment forum.<br>
<br>
Mages are distinguished as being the only casters without either root, snare, or fear.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hurk>Hurk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(11/24/02 6:18:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7956.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   more than that</span><hr size=1> no, mages are defined as having no internal crowd control at all until PoP.  the pet is the only method of control you get, used properly, its extremely powerful, but limited.<br>
<br>
since pets are now beta nuetral, there is no reason not to have one up (even when traveling in unsafe areas to act as a speed bump) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farmatyr1>farmatyr1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#333333>(11/24/02 8:32:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7956.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: more than that</span><hr size=1> Incorrect, Beastlords also have no root or snare, unless you count the class AA that allows their pet to pet to proc a 24 second snare.<br>
<br>
There are no easy to obtain items that have root or snare. Don't bother trying to find the hard to get stuff. It isn't worth it. Learn to play without snare.<br>
<br>
(of course, pure melees have no root or snare either, unless you include the warrior/ranger snare whip, or the 1hb off tunare) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qanamilrafiki>Qanamil Rafiki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 240<br> <font color=#333333>(11/24/02 7:53:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7956.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: more than that</span><hr size=1> Um, crystalline silk nets in CC are quite easy to get, and have effect: root on 'em.<br>
<br>
<br>
-Qanamil Rafiki <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=imaginos9>Imaginos9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The UI Guy</span><br>  Posts: 1001<br> <font color=#333333>(11/25/02 12:52:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7956.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: more than that</span><hr size=1> the dice bag quest in stonebrunt yields a 5 charge snare item. Kill the prince in warrens till he drops bag, turn bag in to kerran child in stonebrunt.<br>
